      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:61:21",
      "text": [
        " يَقْتُلُهُ الْأَدْنَى فَالْأَدْنَى قَبْلَ أَنْ يَرْفَعَهُ إِلَى الْإِمَامِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Hisham Bin Salim, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having been asked about the one who insults Rasool-Allah<sup>saww</sup>. So he<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘He should be killed for the lowest (of insults), as a minimum, before he is brought to the Imam<sup>asws</sup>’."
        ]
      }
